Thanks to everyone who turned out for Charleston’s first Slow Wine tasting at The Wonderer. Over 70 curious consumers came out to learn about the ethos of @slowfoodchs Slow Food Charleston, Slow Wine and the winemakers dedicated to good, clean, and fair practices. We poured through all of the bottle donations from @anthillfarms @carbonistewine @mdcwine @massicanwinery @matthiasson_wine and @tiliawines. We had 🦪 from @barrierislandoysters and produce from @growfoodcarolina turned into beautiful dishes paired to organic meat and fish by Chef Tom at @thewondererchs. Thanks to all of our fabulous volunteers and the venue staff for your fun professionalism. We sold a ton of wine and the tickets only cost $25 dollars (free for club members.) An absolute steal. We received so many compliments about the event evoking the old days when Charleston food and wine experiences could be had for a song instead of the hundreds of dollars most experiences cost today. We look forward to hosting a second event sometime this summer! Keep an eye out for news and don’t miss the second best deal of the year when we throw our next fete. 

Special thanks to Kellie Jeanne Holmes for sourcing wine and running the show and Carrie Larson for her input and support and all the other members of Slow Food Charleston who came out to help and hang out. ❤️❤️❤️❤️
